<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-21T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="608" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/454: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Goold</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-21T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">April 21,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>17. Legation’s despatch No. 3, March 1, 1919.<note n="3" xml:id="d608fn3"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_731"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                                    731</ref>.</note> Advice and consent of the Senate to the
                            ratification of the Treaty as amended by agreement with Colombian
                            Government was given yesterday without further amendments. Vote was 69
                            to 19. Inform Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>